CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1962, page 8, reads: "Cutting Cake - Mr. and Mrs. Leroy Townsend cut their wedding cake at the reception which followed their recent marriage at Calvary Baptist Church. The bride is the former Mrs. Mildred Burgess. The Rev. James A. Cox, assisted by the Rev. Robert Brown, officiated at the rites. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Bride, Mildred Burgess Townsend, wearing short floral veil and light colored jacquard suit, posed with groom, wearing Leroy Townsend, behind four tiered wedding cake, in Calvary Baptist Church
